WEBVTT

1
00:00:26.861 --> 00:00:29.196
Hey. Reggie! Get up!

2
00:00:37.997 --> 00:00:39.039
Fuck!

3
00:00:56.599 --> 00:00:58.517
I hear you're too sick to practice.

4
00:00:59.393 --> 00:01:00.728
I feel better. Coach.

5
00:01:02.980 --> 00:01:05.107
When was the last time you had a decent meal?

6
00:01:05.775 --> 00:01:06.776
Come on.

7
00:01:07.359 --> 00:01:09.570
Mary's always happy to see you at the table.

8
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:11.822
Nothing you say will change my mind.

9
00:01:11.906 --> 00:01:13.115
Damn it. Reggie.

10
00:01:13.866 --> 00:01:16.535
You're the most talented
superhero I know.

11
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:21.582
And you throw it all away.
to sell coke to gangs?

12
00:01:21.665 --> 00:01:24.293
You don't know me. Coach. You don't know anything about me.

13
00:01:24.376 --> 00:01:25.544
I know you have a heart.

14
00:01:26.295 --> 00:01:28.005
I know you want more than that.

15
00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:29.423
You have a choice. son.

16
00:01:30.007 --> 00:01:31.717
Either you run away from this life.

17
00:01:32.635 --> 00:01:35.304
or you're gonna have an early funeral.

18
00:01:35.721 --> 00:01:38.724
I'm your good old Coach Brink.

19
00:01:39.767 --> 00:01:41.477
Come back with me.

20
00:01:42.311 --> 00:01:43.521
In the suburbs.

21
00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:47.358
It doesn't matter what I want.

22
00:01:48.818 --> 00:01:50.486
I'll never get out of here.

23
00:01:50.569 --> 00:01:52.988
-Stop! Damn it!
-Stop right there.

24
00:01:53.072 --> 00:01:55.449
Dude. that couldn't have been better!

25
00:01:55.533 --> 00:01:58.619
That was fucking perfect! Let's do it again.

26
00:01:58.702 --> 00:02:01.580
Ferelle. you're like Streep.
It made me cry.

27
00:02:02.373 --> 00:02:04.124
Literally.

28
00:02:04.208 --> 00:02:07.962
Now you're glad you spent two weeks
at the youth center in Compton. right?

29
00:02:08.045 --> 00:02:10.256
Don't I play it much like Birth of a Champion?

30
00:02:10.339 --> 00:02:13.717
And that's supposed to be a bad thing?
Wait. what's that smell?

31
00:02:13.801 --> 00:02:17.221
-Everybody stop! What's that smell?
-What?

32
00:02:17.304 --> 00:02:18.305
It's...

33
00:02:18.848 --> 00:02:21.016
-Is that you?
-I was eating falafel.

34
00:02:21.851 --> 00:02:22.852
What?

35
00:02:23.519 --> 00:02:25.312
I smell an Oscar nomination.

36
00:02:25.396 --> 00:02:26.647
Give it a rest!

37
00:02:26.730 --> 00:02:29.400
-I don't.
-Don't say it. -Don't say it.

38
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:30.901
You can't jinx this.

39
00:02:30.985 --> 00:02:33.988
You better make room
on the shelf. De Niro. Okay?

40
00:02:34.071 --> 00:02:35.865
Okay. Starting again.

41
00:02:35.948 --> 00:02:37.700
-I'll see how it went.
-Clearly.

42
00:02:37.783 --> 00:02:39.952
Give him the headphones! Thank you. sir.

43
00:02:40.035 --> 00:02:43.038
One quick thing just between us.

44
00:02:43.122 --> 00:02:46.292
It's like you're having trouble getting it going.

45
00:02:47.501 --> 00:02:49.003
Maybe it's the scene.

46
00:02:49.086 --> 00:02:50.629
It's a brilliant scene. Look at this.

47
00:02:50.713 --> 00:02:54.216
this is in the story
in your character's story. You understand?

48
00:02:54.300 --> 00:02:57.511
Everybody broke a stick over you.
you're all alone until coach...

49
00:02:57.595 --> 00:02:59.597
Doesn't he pull out of the ghetto like a savior?

50
00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:03.225
No. you're actually saving each other.
it's a perfectly balanced story.

51
00:03:03.309 --> 00:03:06.186
All consultants
social sensitivity consultants agree.

52
00:03:06.270 --> 00:03:08.188
My brother was my only coach.

53
00:03:08.272 --> 00:03:09.106
Okay?

54
00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:12.610
He was a waiter at a pizza place.
he wasn't a crack dealer.

55
00:03:13.611 --> 00:03:15.738
And now he must be really proud of you.

56
00:03:15.821 --> 00:03:18.407
Let's run it again. shall we?

57
00:03:20.826 --> 00:03:22.161
-Give me a minute.
-Clearly.

58
00:03:23.245 --> 00:03:25.956
Wait. you know what? One more thing.

59
00:03:26.040 --> 00:03:29.126
You said. "It doesn't matter what I want."

60
00:03:29.209 --> 00:03:32.713
But in the script.
"What I want doesn't matter."

61
00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:35.466
Yeah? Let's do it.

62
00:03:35.549 --> 00:03:37.635
All right. everybody on your marks.

63
00:03:37.718 --> 00:03:39.219
Let's film it!

64
00:03:42.389 --> 00:03:44.183
Can we talk?

65
00:03:44.266 --> 00:03:46.602
You're not talking.
that's your telltale sign.

66
00:03:46.685 --> 00:03:48.646
Playing Noir is a great challenge.

67
00:03:48.729 --> 00:03:50.314
But yesterday was really weird.

68
00:03:50.397 --> 00:03:52.816
I've never killed anyone before.

69
00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:54.985
Does Homelander make us kill people a lot?

70
00:03:55.069 --> 00:03:57.196
And if we do. do we just do it?

71
00:03:58.656 --> 00:04:00.783
Don't get me wrong.
I'm thrilled to be here.

72
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:03.452
And I'll take it all.

73
00:04:03.535 --> 00:04:06.372
But I have a problem
with Noir's motivation. You get it. right?

74
00:04:06.455 --> 00:04:08.248
His motivation is to be a freak.

75
00:04:08.332 --> 00:04:10.042
Just shut up and keep up.

76
00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:11.835
Do as you're told.

77
00:04:15.089 --> 00:04:19.176
Violence in our bloody streets
against decent. hardworking Americans.

78
00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:22.262
If you're considering letting
your children to play carefree

79
00:04:22.346 --> 00:04:24.890
outdoors unsupervised. you'd better think twice.

80
00:04:24.974 --> 00:04:28.394
These two animals.
Benny Long and Ian Rashford

81
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:32.022
outside the courthouse yesterday
beat three decent men to death.

82
00:04:32.106 --> 00:04:34.608
Starlight fans
have revealed their true colors.

83
00:04:34.692 --> 00:04:38.195
They were causing a disturbance
at several "peaceful demonstrations"

84
00:04:38.278 --> 00:04:39.989
all over the country.

85
00:04:40.072 --> 00:04:43.575
I personally don't take civil liberties
in our beautiful country as a matter of course.

86
00:04:43.659 --> 00:04:46.120
But Starlight fans
seem to see it differently.

87
00:04:46.203 --> 00:04:49.081
Okay. soy for the pH.

88
00:04:49.164 --> 00:04:52.960
hyaluronic acid
for deep moisturizing and arginine for...

89
00:04:53.043 --> 00:04:54.169
What's it all for?

90
00:04:54.253 --> 00:04:56.088
I'm a Voughtality dealer.

91
00:04:56.171 --> 00:04:58.424
I'm five thousand points short.
to get a Cadillac.

92
00:04:58.507 --> 00:05:03.053
-Might help...
-You work for Vought?

93
00:05:03.137 --> 00:05:05.097
Voughtality. "For the super-tebe."

94
00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:07.349
You know that Vought
killed my girlfriend. right?

95
00:05:08.600 --> 00:05:10.519
I'm fighting them.

96
00:05:12.604 --> 00:05:15.232
I think I have rosemary oil.

97
00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.942
It's really good for the joints.

98
00:05:17.026 --> 00:05:19.319
Could you just... Can you stop. please?

99
00:05:19.403 --> 00:05:22.781
-Please stop. Stop it!
-I'm sorry.

100
00:05:22.865 --> 00:05:25.659
Oh. God. I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I was just...

101
00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:28.412
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

102
00:05:30.247 --> 00:05:31.331
You look good.

103
00:05:31.749 --> 00:05:32.916
You've grown up.

104
00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:35.210
Yeah. it fits.
because you've seen the last of me.

105
00:05:35.294 --> 00:05:37.755
-when I was six!
-Don't yell at me. please.

106
00:05:37.838 --> 00:05:40.132
-What are you doing here?
-I got a call from the hospital.

107
00:05:40.215 --> 00:05:43.510
Yeah. when they couldn't reach me.
But I'm here now. so...

108
00:05:44.553 --> 00:05:46.638
He doesn't need you. Neither one of us does.

109
00:05:46.722 --> 00:05:48.057
Dad didn't tell you?

110
00:05:49.391 --> 00:05:50.225
Damn it.

111
00:05:51.727 --> 00:05:52.853
So what?

112
00:05:52.936 --> 00:05:57.524
He gave me power of attorney.
including medical decisions.

113
00:05:57.608 --> 00:05:59.568
and signed the DNR.

114
00:06:00.194 --> 00:06:01.737
Didn't he update his will?

115
00:06:02.237 --> 00:06:03.238
Oh. yeah.

116
00:06:05.324 --> 00:06:08.285
Why would he give power of attorney
to you and not me?

117
00:06:08.368 --> 00:06:10.704
I know. I know. We've been in touch...

118
00:06:11.497 --> 00:06:13.165
The last year or two.

119
00:06:13.749 --> 00:06:16.543
Here and there. But ask him.

120
00:06:16.627 --> 00:06:17.753
But. Hughie. don't worry.

121
00:06:17.836 --> 00:06:19.671
-I'm really good in a crisis.
-Don't...

122
00:06:19.755 --> 00:06:22.299
And I can handle it.

123
00:06:22.925 --> 00:06:24.093
I promise.

124
00:06:27.054 --> 00:06:28.263
You promise?

125
00:06:30.516 --> 00:06:32.351
Hughie. wait!

126
00:06:48.367 --> 00:06:50.202
Stealing out?

127
00:06:55.207 --> 00:06:56.959
I didn't mean to wake you.

128
00:06:58.752 --> 00:06:59.586
Hey. Hey.

129
00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:04.466
Maybe you should stay in bed tonight.

130
00:07:04.550 --> 00:07:05.467
Yeah. I'm fine.

131
00:07:08.512 --> 00:07:09.930
It could have been a lot worse.

132
00:07:10.597 --> 00:07:13.392
I mean. it would have been if you hadn't shown up.

133
00:07:18.564 --> 00:07:19.481
Thank you.

134
00:07:30.117 --> 00:07:30.951
Work.

135
00:07:42.129 --> 00:07:43.714
Your speech therapist Gloria

136
00:07:43.797 --> 00:07:46.216
told me how much progress you've made.

137
00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:47.467
How's it going?

138
00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:56.476
If it goes well. I'm not here.

139
00:07:57.561 --> 00:08:00.355
You know. elective mutism

140
00:08:00.439 --> 00:08:04.318
is often a symptom of trauma.

141
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:05.777
What do you think?

142
00:08:10.532 --> 00:08:12.075
Our past does not shape us.

143
00:08:12.159 --> 00:08:14.369
I agree with that. but sometimes you have to

144
00:08:14.453 --> 00:08:16.830
to confront his past.
to break away from it.

145
00:08:19.166 --> 00:08:21.752
Why don't we start with something simple?

146
00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:23.837
Tell me about your parents.

147
00:08:32.930 --> 00:08:35.015
Christ. Is that what you're telling us now?

148
00:08:35.098 --> 00:08:37.809
Have you been to the doctor? Have you...

149
00:08:37.893 --> 00:08:40.437
-How long do you have left?
-It's none of your business.

150
00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:42.731
What's going on?

151
00:08:42.814 --> 00:08:45.651
I don't know why I'm telling you this.
But I'm knocking on heaven's gate

152
00:08:45.734 --> 00:08:47.194
and it's really pissing me off.

153
00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:49.905
I was trying to warn you.
that this shit is poisonous.

154
00:08:49.988 --> 00:08:51.406
You're not one of us.

155
00:08:51.490 --> 00:08:52.574
-Hell!
-That's enough.

156
00:08:55.035 --> 00:08:56.453
Let's talk.

157
00:09:08.507 --> 00:09:10.384
-You're out.
-What do you mean?

158
00:09:10.467 --> 00:09:12.344
I'm firing you. Pack up and get out.

159
00:09:12.427 --> 00:09:14.680
So. I'm speaking plainly
and that's what I get?

160
00:09:14.763 --> 00:09:17.557
Fuck me. Is this where honesty gets you?

161
00:09:17.641 --> 00:09:20.352
Honesty? You've been lying to us for the last six months.

162
00:09:20.435 --> 00:09:22.104
Not saying something is not lying.

163
00:09:22.187 --> 00:09:24.940
Look. you need all the help you can get.
that's available to you.

164
00:09:25.023 --> 00:09:27.192
Not from you. You're a liability. Butcher.

165
00:09:27.859 --> 00:09:29.861
I'm not gonna let this go to waste.

166
00:09:30.529 --> 00:09:31.822
The gang is my project.

167
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:34.032
Says the man over the grave.
who's bluffing for the last time.

168
00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:38.996
So pack your bags and get the fuck out.

169
00:09:39.913 --> 00:09:41.206
Or I'll hand fire you.

170
00:09:44.418 --> 00:09:47.004
-I just...
-I don't want to hear it. He's outside.

171
00:09:48.380 --> 00:09:50.340
You can join him if you want.

172
00:09:58.307 --> 00:10:01.393
Small-town boy
growing up with his mom on a ranch in Montana.

173
00:10:01.476 --> 00:10:05.063
He's just a regular guy at first glance.

174
00:10:05.147 --> 00:10:07.733
But deep in his heart. he knows
he's different. Special.

175
00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.526
He always asks himself. "Who am I?"

176
00:10:09.609 --> 00:10:11.695
One day this question is answered.

177
00:10:11.778 --> 00:10:14.906
when Homelander comes down from heaven and says

178
00:10:14.990 --> 00:10:17.159
-with tears in my eyes...
-No tears.

179
00:10:17.242 --> 00:10:22.497
And he proudly says: "Son. it's time.
to take your place at my side."

180
00:10:22.581 --> 00:10:25.584
And for Ryan. it's surprising
and yet inevitable.

181
00:10:25.667 --> 00:10:28.378
He always knew he was destined for greatness.

182
00:10:28.462 --> 00:10:30.589
Because it came from greatness.

183
00:10:34.009 --> 00:10:36.094
Wow! See that. son?

184
00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:37.596
What do you think?

185
00:10:38.847 --> 00:10:40.140
It's cool.

186
00:10:41.308 --> 00:10:42.142
I guess.

187
00:10:42.976 --> 00:10:44.394
I guess?

188
00:10:46.021 --> 00:10:49.149
-I think it looks amazing.
-Absolutely amazing.

189
00:10:49.232 --> 00:10:50.776
-It's gonna be a bust.
-Great. -Great.

190
00:10:50.859 --> 00:10:51.902
This whole thing sucks.

191
00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:55.822
It doesn't suck.

192
00:10:55.906 --> 00:10:58.784
It sucks like a sled in the summer.

193
00:10:58.867 --> 00:11:00.786
I'm sorry. but why are you here?

194
00:11:00.869 --> 00:11:03.288
After Gunpowder
Vought got rid of the snitches.

195
00:11:03.372 --> 00:11:04.998
Compensation exceeded profitability.

196
00:11:05.082 --> 00:11:09.044
I don't think he'd think of me
Ryan complained to HR.

197
00:11:10.337 --> 00:11:11.546
So what?

198
00:11:11.630 --> 00:11:15.467
Ryan is the first born superhero
and his brand needs to reflect that.

199
00:11:15.550 --> 00:11:18.178
It's not one of the lab shots.

200
00:11:18.261 --> 00:11:20.180
He was chosen by fate. by God.

201
00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:23.100
anything to be the one to save the world.

202
00:11:23.183 --> 00:11:24.309
Yes.

203
00:11:24.393 --> 00:11:29.439
but let's not forget why he's special. right?

204
00:11:29.523 --> 00:11:30.899
He's my son.

205
00:11:30.982 --> 00:11:32.818
Chosen by God. sure.

206
00:11:32.901 --> 00:11:35.737
But... made by me.

207
00:11:35.821 --> 00:11:39.616
The story of the "chosen one" only works if.
when it stands on its own.

208
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:42.911
Harry Potter. Neo. Luke Skywalker.

209
00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:46.373
Hollywood trained people.
to love the white lonely savior.

210
00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:49.751
America will want to fall in love with Ryan.

211
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.587
VOUGHT
OVERVIEW OF INTERNATIONAL CRIME

212
00:11:52.671 --> 00:11:53.755
What's that?

213
00:11:53.839 --> 00:11:57.300
International criminals.
Your first rescue. Congratulations. son.

214
00:11:58.844 --> 00:12:00.178
My name's not on it.

215
00:12:00.262 --> 00:12:02.848
You wanted a kingdom for your son.

216
00:12:02.931 --> 00:12:05.517
I'm helping you build it.

217
00:12:12.149 --> 00:12:14.651
Well done. Just as we agreed.

218
00:12:15.569 --> 00:12:17.028
Here you go.

219
00:12:17.362 --> 00:12:18.280
Thank you.

220
00:12:19.948 --> 00:12:20.991
Can I?

221
00:12:23.994 --> 00:12:26.580
I'm here because Homelander wants me here.

222
00:12:26.663 --> 00:12:28.081
Because he trusts me.

223
00:12:57.736 --> 00:13:01.907
Listen. I know. I know.
you're the smartest woman on earth.

224
00:13:01.990 --> 00:13:03.742
The smartest man.

225
00:13:05.243 --> 00:13:06.870
Let me give you some advice.

226
00:13:06.953 --> 00:13:08.872
Women are supposed to support each other.

227
00:13:10.207 --> 00:13:12.334
You can't talk to Homelander like that.

228
00:13:12.417 --> 00:13:13.543
I'm telling the truth.

229
00:13:13.627 --> 00:13:16.254
You're the one who's so afraid of him.
that you pulled your hair out.

230
00:13:16.338 --> 00:13:18.423
If I were you. I'd be useful for something.

231
00:13:18.507 --> 00:13:21.968
A little breast milk.
so she'll have a breast to latch on to.

232
00:13:22.052 --> 00:13:24.137
before you end up like Madelyn Stillwell.

233
00:13:27.265 --> 00:13:29.726
Hey. Ashley. How you doing?

234
00:13:29.809 --> 00:13:31.811
I was just coming to see you. boss.

235
00:13:31.895 --> 00:13:33.563
I've been looking everywhere for you.

236
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:37.359
I heard.
Ryan's going on his first solo job.

237
00:13:37.442 --> 00:13:39.819
I want to talk to you about something. I have an idea.

238
00:13:39.903 --> 00:13:42.864
So what if...

239
00:13:43.281 --> 00:13:44.908
Just hear me out. please.

240
00:13:44.991 --> 00:13:47.702
What if I'd been there?

241
00:13:50.455 --> 00:13:52.374
That's all. That's my whole proposal.

242
00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:56.127
Want to action acceptable for the whole family?

243
00:13:57.837 --> 00:14:01.383
While PETA has you
still on the animal scum list?

244
00:14:03.635 --> 00:14:04.844
I swear to God.

245
00:14:05.387 --> 00:14:10.016
Fools who think they're smart.
are the fucking worst!

246
00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:14.187
Why do you let her talk to you like that?

247
00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:16.565
She's a stupid bitch.

248
00:14:16.648 --> 00:14:18.608
I guess he has his days.

249
00:14:18.692 --> 00:14:20.193
It's like a full moon. isn't it?

250
00:14:20.277 --> 00:14:22.404
You are a genetically superior being

251
00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:25.240
and she's the evolutionary equivalent of a capybara.

252
00:14:25.323 --> 00:14:28.660
-Cappuccino?
-It's a giant rodent from South America.

253
00:14:29.202 --> 00:14:31.830
You're better than her. Act like it.

254
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:34.666
And you should be at the event.

255
00:14:35.584 --> 00:14:36.543
